      .outer-container
        .homemiddle
          .circlepics
            a(href='/solar')
              img.solar-pic(src='public/solar_home.jpg')
            a(href='/wind')
              img.wind-pic(src='public/wind_home.jpg')
            a(href='/hydropower')
              img.hydro-pic(src='public/hydroelectric_home.jpg')
            a(href='/geothermal')
              img.geo-pic(src='public/geothermal_home.jpg')
          .description
            p.default-desc Hover over and find out a little about each alternative.
            p.solar-desc(style='opacity: 0;')
              | Solar energy, the most popular home alternative, can be used to drastically lower the costs of daily living by converting energy from the sun into energy that can be used to power homes.
            p.wind-desc(style='opacity: 0;')
              | Wind energy converts the wind's force into mechanical power to help generate power for homes, therefore saving large amount of money in the long run.
            p.hydro-desc(style='opacity: 0;')
              | Hydropower transforms the energy of flowing water into electricity using simple mechanics which is then used for homes and drastically lowers costs when compared to a previous installed system.
            p.geo-desc(style='opacity: 0;')
              | Geothermal energy can be used to cut expenses by producing energy generated by heat stored beneath the Earth's surface for your home.
        .divider
          .inner-divider
        .container
          h2 Why Nero?
          br
          p
            | Nero provides the information about four main types of alternative energy sources: solar, wind, hydropower, and geothermal. The information found on our site can greatly help a homeowner living in the United States determine what alternative energy source is right for them by taking their budget and geographical locations into consideration. This site is designed to give information such as what the source actually is, how it is used, the geographical locations in which it will be most effective, the cost range for the systems, and the amount of money it would save over time!
        .divider
          .inner-divider
        .container
          h2 A Little Bit About Nero
          br
          p
            | Nero stands for New Energy Resource Options. Nero was also a Roman emperor who ruled during 54-69 AD. The people of Rome speculated that Nero was behind the Great Fire of Rome and that he nearly destroyed the entire city of Rome with fire which was the first source of energy. Emperor Nero was also greatly acknowledged for taking things like sports, trade, architecture, etc. and enhancing them just as we are doing today. We are taking something traditional, like electricity, and showing how homeowners can enhance it by using the nature around them such as the sun, wind, water, and the earth!
